Package de.tub.pes.syscir.engine.transformers

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    KnownFunctionTransformer
    This is the base interface for every known function transformer in STATE.
    KnownTypeTransformer
    This is the base interface for every known type transformer in STATE.
    Transformer
    A transformer in this context is a class that is able to process specific XML nodes that represent nodes in a SystemC abstract syntax tree of KaSCPar format.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractTransformer  
    AbstractType  
    AccessSpecifierTransformer
    this class saves the current access-level in the appropriate environment-variable
    ArgumentsTransformer
    every functioncall has an argumentlist this list starts with the arguments-tag every Expression inside of this Tag is an argument these expressions will be saved on the stack, when they handled after all childnodes of the argumentstag are handled we take them from the expressionstack an put them in the argument-list
    ArrayAccessExpressionTransformer
    every time an Array is accessed, we need to know the indices first we need all primary-expressions in the first, the Array is specified the other ones specifies the indices we handle the childenodes of every primary-tag after we handle the first primary-tag we have an variable-expression on the stack, we check if we have an array if its true, we keep it, and set a boolean true so all other primary-expressions contain the index-descriptions we put them into a list then we build a new ArrayAccessExpression and push it on the stack
    ArrayInitializerTransformer
    at the arrayinitializer-tag the Array is already declared now we need to handle the childnodes every element is descripted as a expression every time we handle a childnode the lastInitializer-Variable of the environment is set we take it and put it in the ArrayInitializerExpression After we handled all childnodes, we push this expression in the stack a multidimensional Array is initialized as array of array-initalizers
    AssignmentTransformer
    an assignment-tag has 2 childnodes, the first childnode is the left-element where the right-element, the second childnode, is assigned to we save an assignment as binary-expression after the childnodehandling the topelement of the stack is the right-element and the next element is the left-element if we have a childnode named assignment_expression_operator we take the assignment-operator from him, otherwise its the "="
    BaseSpecifierTransformer
    this class handles the baseSpecifier tag which represents the inheritation of modules and Structs we know the current modul or the current struct if we found a common reference to sc-module we don't set a reference, we create an empty module same thing if we found a reference to sc_channel, but at this time we mark the current object as channel same way if we found a reference to sc_prim_channel otherwise we look in the module-list and the struct-list for an object with the same name if we found one, we add the reference of it to the current object if not, we create a new object, add it to the list and add a reference of the new one to the current object
    BinaryOperatorTransformer
    if we found a binary-operator-tag we need the right and the leftside of the operator and the operator itself we handle the child-nodes, if the stack is to small or if one of the two expressions is null we report an error otherwise we extract the right operator and build a new binaryexpression and push it to the stack
    BlockStatementTransformer
    a blockstatment-tag marks one line in the code but sometimes a blockstatment-tag is a child of a blockstatment-tag both cases have to be handled different if its the head-blockstatment we remeber it, clear the expression-stack handle the childnodes and add all Expressions in the right order to the current function at hte second case we only handle the childnodes
    BlockTransformer
    the Block-tag contains the body of a function we save all Childnodes and put them into a list so we can handle them later but if we ar already inside of a functionblock , we handle this chidlnodes
    BreakStatementTransformer
    this class only creates a new Breakstatmentexpression<
    BuiltinTypeSpecifierTransformer
    In this class we handle the BuiltinTypeSpecifier-Tag we extract the name of the type and if some exist, the suptype and the length
    ClassSpecifierTransformer
    this tag starts a new object-description we check if its a new module or a new struct then we check if this object already exist, for example it is a father-object from another and was created in the BaseSpecifierTransformer we put it in the appropriate list and set a reference to the right "current"-Variable in the environment
    ConstantTransformer
    if the tag has a value-attribute, we extract it, look weather there are subinformations and create a new constant-expression if we found out, thats a Timeunit, we create a new Variable and a new variable-expression no matter what it is, we push the expression on the stack if it hasn't a value-attribute, we only handle the childnodes
    ContinueStatementTransformer
    this class only creates a new Continuestatmentexpression<
    CTORDefinitionTransformer
    with this tag we found the constructor of the current object we create a dummyfunction and parse the parameters of the function we also save the body we create a new SCFunction add the parameter and put it to the functionlist of the current object we also that the constructor-variable of the current object
    DefaultTransformer
    only handle the childnodes of the actual tag
    DoNothingTransformer  
    DoStatementTransformer
    we have a do-while-loop we extract the block which represents the loop-body then we search for the condition to parse it and save it afterwards we handle the loop-body at the end we create a new loopExpression and add it to the stack
    ForStatementTransformer
    we search for the 3 Expressions which control the for-loop the for_init, the for_condition and the for_update we save them, and handle the loop-body afterwards we creat a new forLoopExpression and add it to the stack
    FunctionDefinitionTransformer
    first we handle the childnodes of the function their we found the returntype, the name, the parameter and the scope-overwrite if their isn't a scope-overwrite, we have a normal function, so we create a new one we have to check if we are in a module, a struct, or if its a global function, we add it at the right place and create a new entry in the functionbody-map if necessary and add the functionbody if their is a scope we do nearly the same, but we look for a module or a struct with the name of the scope and add the function their if we found one if we didn't found a module with this name neither a struct, we assume its a global function
    IDExpressionTransformer
    we found a name, but we didn't know if we have a variable, a event, a port or sockets, a module instance or a function we check it in this order, on trying to find it with the getters of the current functions or the current object if we found something with this name, we create a new Expression, corresponding to the case if we didn't found something, we assume its a new function and create one and build a new expression
    IfStatementTransformer
    first we handle the first real childnode, thats the condition afterwards we get all childnodes named "block" we handle the first one, cause this is the then-case then we look if we have an other block in the list, thats the else-case, and handle it then we build a new IfElseExpression and puch it to the stack
    InitDeclaratorListTransformer
    we clear the type and handle the childnodes, where the type will be set the declaration of the new variable also happens their
    InitDeclaratorTransformer
    First we try to find 3 different childnodes, the declarator, the qulified_id and the declarator_suffixes we get the last type-modifiers and save them, if their is a static or a const we set the appropriate boolean true the oter modifiers a saved in a list we also get the subtypes if found if we havn't found a childnode, qualified_id, we have a pointer so we get the nessecary arguments and create one, then we add it to the current function.
    InitializerTransformer
    we prepare and do the follow-up-stuff of the initialization-handling here we clear the initializer and handle the childnodes if one expression for the initialization is found we pop this from the stack and set the variable of the environment if none ist found, we set the variable null
    MemberDeclarationTransformer
    we clear the type and the modifiers at this point then we handle the childnodes where this variables should be set
    MemberDeclaratorListTransformer
    we clear the type and then handle the childnode, where the type will be set and a new member would be created
    MemberDeclaratorTransformer
    First we try to find 3 different childnodes, the declarator, the qulified_id and the declarator_suffixes we get the last type-modifiers and save them, if their is a static or a const we set the appropriate boolean true the oter modifiers a saved in a list we also get the subtypes if found if we havn't found a childnode, qualified_id, we have a pointer so we get the nessecary arguments and create one, then we add it to the current object.
    NotAllowedTransformer
    This transformer only prints an error message that says that it is not allowed to be used.
    ParameterDeclarationTransformer
    first we get the childe-nodes named declaration_specifiers and declarator if the declarator doesn't exist, we have no parameter otherwise we get the qualified_id-childenode, it it exist, we have a pointer then we get the pointertype and save it for later-construction next step is to get the subtypes, the name and the type then we create a Variable, correspondig to the type, which represent the parameter and add it to the list
    ParameterListTransformer
    we prepare the environment for the parameter-parsing
    PostfixExpressionTransformer  
    PrePostModifierTransformer
    first we handle the childnode then we get the top-expression from the stack next step is, get the real type of the node and create the right unary-expression and add it to the stack
    QualifiedIdTransformer
    we get the name-attribute from the current node and push that on the qualified_id-stack if this node has a child-node, named scope, we get the scope and set the corresponding environment-variable
    QualifiedTypeTransformer
    first we get se childnode named qualified-id and get the name-attribute, this is the type then we search for the template_argument_list, which ware the subtypes, and handle them
    QuestionmarkExpressionTransformer
    a questionmark-expression is similar to an ifElseExpression first we get all real childnodes, if we found less then 3 we have to few then we get the first three nodes, the first is the condition the second the if-case the third the else-case we handle all and remember the found expression with this three expressions we build the new questionmarkexpression
    ReturnStatementTransformer
    we handle the childnode and get the top expression from the stack, this is the returned value if their wasn't an expression nothing is returned then we create a new returnExpression and add it to the stack
    SCClockType  
    SCFifoType  
    SCMainDeclarationTransformer
    we have found the main-function so we serach for the parameters, handle them, get the return-type and the name of this function and build a new function, which we add to the global-systemfucntions we also get the block-node, where the function-body is described we saved it for later
    SCMethodBlockTransformer
    we clear the arguments of a scmethod, so we can handle the childnode where they are declared with this arguments we create a new scmethod and add it to the curren module
    SCMethodTransformer
    we get the name of the function which is declared as method and put it to the corresponding environment-variable
    SCMutexType  
    SCNotifyTransformer  
    SCPortSpecifierTransformer
    first we get the portType according to this type, we set the lastPortSocketType in the environment and handle the childnodes afterwards we create a new known-type because the channel-types are knowntypes
    SCSensitiveTransformer  
    SCSignalType  
    SCThreadBlockTransformer
    we clear the arguments of a scthread, so we can handle the childnode where they are declared with this arguments we create a new scthread and add it to the current module
    SCThreadTransformer
    we get the name of the function which is declared as method and put it to the corresponding environment-variable
    StorageClassSpecifierTransformer
    we get the name-attribute from this tag, its a type-modifier
    SuperClassInitTransformer  
    SwitchStatementTransformer
    first we handle the first real childnode, their we found the switch-value We create a new switchexpression.
    SystemCRoutineTransformer
    a systemC-routine is a function of the SystemC-Standart if its name is "dont_initialize" we only set the process-modifier otherwise we handle the childnodes we get an argumentlist, we create a parameterlist out of the argumentlist then we create a new function and afterwards a new functionexpression which we push to the stack
    TemplateArgumentTransformer
    we get the type and add its name to the last_typeargumentslist
    ThisNodeTransformer
    we create a new instance of the current object and create a corresponding expression, which we add to the stack
    TLMFwBwIF  
    TLMSyncEnumType  
    TypeQualifierTransformer
    we get the name-attribute and add it to the typemodifier-list for later-use
    UnaryExpressionTransformer
    first we get the operator, then we get the connected expression corresponding to the operator we create some expressions and add the unaryexpression to the stackS
    WhileStatementTransformer
    first we handle the first real childnode, this is the condition afterwards we handle the block-child, which is the loop-body then we build a new expression and add it to the stack
